title: Montezuma's Castle and Other Weird Tales
creator: Charles B. Cory
description: LibriVox recording of Montezuma's Castle and Other Weird Tales by Charles B. Cory. Read by LibriVox Volunteers This is a collection of weird tales inspired from the natural history expeditions of the author, an independently wealthy bird collector, Olympic golfer, writer of many books on birds of the world, and, as evidenced in these pages, a fine storyteller to boot. (Summary by A. Gramour) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (93MB)
subject: llibrivox; audiobooks; Mummies; Ghosts; Voodoo; Occult; Telepathy; Explorers; Natural History
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
I LOVED these stories! Mr Cory really writes some great short stories that are rather unique.  Most are a bit on the dark side, but they all are quite enjoyable!  Very reminiscent of Ambrose Bierce.  The readers all did a fine job to boot! Any fan of Bierce is guaranteed to love these stories also! 

Great writing and great reading make this selection five stars in my book!  Download and listen, I promise you won't be disappointed!
